Software & Tools: Oracle11g, PLSQL Developer,TOAD

The Purpose of eCustomer is to provide a 360-degree view of the customer linked across functional silos. Customer Registry (CR) built by eCustomer, maintains an enterprise-wide database directory of current and potential Cisco customers. It contains cleansed, enriched, and standardized customer data with each CR customer having its own unique CR ID. Partner Go to Market View (PGTMV) within CR is an Alternate view, tasked with providing Channels Sales and Operations unit, a globally consistent hierarchy of partner data that resides in Customer Registry (CR). Alternate Party view (APV) provides the functionality to business to create the alternate hierarchy based on individual business needs. It allows business to group business relevant parties and maintains the hierarchical relationship among the selected parties to create functional view. The operations performed on these alternate views (APV hierarchies) are captured in CR and published as an event to subscribing systems through CRES (Customer Registry Enterprise Services - Tibco based solution) Services. Any operation performed on APV hierarchy will be captured and logged by CR process tracking the changes on APV. The scheduled job will capture all these changes in APV and stores it in event log table. Based on these notification events CRES extract process picks up data and populate CRES publishing table. The CRES publishing table is flat table object which provides the APV hierarchy and attributes information in CR standard format. This information message is delivered to those source systems which are configured in CR to receive this message through CRES - EA: Tibco based message publish- subscription service.

